        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 10:50PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 1050 PM CDT, strong thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 10 miles east of Port Of Raymond to 9 miles northwest
of Grenora to 12 miles west of Bonetrail. Movement was east at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Grenora, Fortuna, Alkabo, Writing Rock State Historical Site,
Bonetrail, Hanks City, Zahl, Appam, Hanks, and Blacktail Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, seek shelter inside a building.</instruction>
